<h2 id="data-transformers">Data Transformers <a class="headerlink" href="date-format-sanity-validation#data-transformers" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>So I keep telling you that the purpose of the field "types" is to control how a field
is rendered. But that's only <em>half</em> of it. Behind the scenes, many fields have a
"data transformer".</p>
<p>Basically, the job of a data transformer is to transform the data that's inside of
your PHP code to a format that's visible to your user. For example, the <code>firstDiscoveredAt</code>
value on <code>Genus</code> is actually a <code>DateTime</code> object:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="06515373da">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
