</p>
<p>The data transformer internally changes that into the string that's printed in the box.</p>
<p>Then, when a date string is submitted, that same data transformer does its work in
reverse: changing the string back into a <code>DateTime</code> object.</p>
<p>The data transformer is also kicking butt on the <code>subFamily</code> field. The <code>id</code> of the
selected <code>SubFamily</code> is submitted. Then, the data transformer uses that to query
for a <code>SubFamily</code> object and set that on <code>Genus</code>.</p>
<p>You don't need to know more about data transformers right now, I just want you to
realize that this awesomeness is happening.</p>

    
